## Troubleshooting

### Native extension compilation error

Ensure build tools are installed:

```bash
# macOS
xcode-select --install

# Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt-get install build-essential ruby-dev

# Windows (via RubyInstaller)
ridk install
```

### "Could not find Kreuzcrawl"

Reinstall the gem:

```bash
gem uninstall kreuzcrawl
gem install kreuzcrawl --no-document
```

### OCR not working

Verify Tesseract is installed:

```bash
tesseract --version
```

## Examples

### Process Directory of PDFs

```ruby
require 'kreuzcrawl'
require 'pathname'

Dir.glob("documents/*.pdf").each do |file|
  puts "Processing: #{file}"
  result = Kreuzcrawl.extract_file(file)
  puts "  Content length: #{result.content.length}"
  puts "  Language: #{result.detected_languages}"
end
```

### Extract and Parse Structured Data

```ruby
require 'kreuzcrawl'
require 'json'

result = Kreuzcrawl.extract_file("data.pdf")

# Parse content as JSON (if applicable)
begin
  data = JSON.parse(result.content)
  puts "Parsed data: #{data}"
rescue JSON::ParserError
  puts "Content is not JSON"
end
```

### Save Extracted Images

```ruby
require 'kreuzcrawl'

config = Kreuzcrawl::ExtractionConfig.new(
  images: Kreuzcrawl::ImageExtractionConfig.new(
    extract_images: true
  )
)

result = Kreuzcrawl.extract_file("document.pdf", config: config)

result.images&.each_with_index do |image, index|
  File.write("image_#{index}.png", image.data)
end
```

